name: acetaldehyde dehydrogenase (acetylating)
classes: Acting on the aldehyde or oxo group of donors;
With NAD+ or NADP+ as acceptor
reaction: acetaldehyde + CoA + NAD+ = acetyl-CoA + NADH + H+ [RN:R00228]
comment: Also acts, more slowly, on glycolaldehyde, propanal and butanal. In several bacterial species this enzyme forms a bifunctional complex with EC 4.1.3.39, 4-hydroxy-2-oxovalerate aldolase. The enzymes from the bacteria Burkholderia xenovorans and Thermus thermophilus also perform the reaction of EC 1.2.1.87, propanal dehydrogenase (propanoylating). Involved in the meta-cleavage pathway for the degradation of phenols, methylphenols and catechols. NADP+ can replace NAD+ but the rate of reaction is much slower [3].
